(Hrafnkell brought his household east over Fljótsdals-herað and right across Fljótsdalr unto the eastern)Tj
T*
(side of Lagarfljót. At the bottom of that water stood a small stead, which was called Lokhylla. This)Tj
T*
(land Hrafnkell bought on credit, for his means went no further than to cover the cost of household)Tj
T*
(implements. People had much talk about this, how Hrafnkell’s masterfulness had suddenly come down)Tj
T*
